  "text": "Microscopically, the serous solid adenoma has the same architectural and cytological characteristics as the serous microcystic cystadenoma, namely, a round or ovoid structure formed of cuboid cells derived from the ductular epithelium. The cytoplasm is rich in glycogen with a small central nucleus [CITATION_1] . The prevalent difference being that the solid adenoma has no secretory activity, giving a more compact structure the main difference is the absence of secretory activity, which confers a more compact structure to this lesion compared to cystic forms. According to the analysis of the different cases, the average size is 2.7 cm among the 22 cases previously described. We also note that a capsule is found in 73% of cases.",
